The paper deals with the deployment of unmanned aerial vehicles (UAVs) as flying base stations (BSs) for optimizing the throughput of mobile users in UAV networks. This involves real-time decision-making in a dynamic environment, which suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of Networked Systems (cs.NI), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Systems and Control (cs.SY). The proposed method uses deep reinforcement learning, which falls under the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves optimization techniques, which could place it under the sub-category of Information Theory (cs.IT).
